</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-iqVWFU kwUChp pf-23_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-24_ pf-text-1"><strong>Historical roots</strong> - The concept of innovation has been studied since the early 20th century, with significant contributions from scholars like Joseph Schumpeter and Everett Rogers.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-26_ pf-text-1"><strong>Modern impact</strong> - Over 80% of executives consider innovation a top priority, yet less than 10% are satisfied with their organisation's innovation performance.
